# File: knowledge_service/requirements-dev.in
# Service: knowledge-service
# Author: Haffey Enterprises LLC
# Created: 2026-07-21
# Revised: 2026-07-21
# Description: Development and test dependency floors for knowledge-service —
#   the runtime set plus the gate toolchain (pytest + coverage, ruff, mypy).
#
#   Deliberate exclusion: `testcontainers`. SDD-001 §6 requires that all domain
#   tests run against the in-memory port doubles and that no service test depend
#   on live Neo4j; a container fixture in this service's suite would contradict
#   that. The containerized graph belongs to the conformance harness
#   (`conformance/`), which is a distinct verification surface (SDD-001 §6).
#   `respx` is likewise absent — no outbound HTTP exists to contract-test yet.

-r requirements.in

pytest
pytest-asyncio
pytest-cov
ruff>=0.4.0
mypy>=1.9.0

# Test client only. The house testing standard's stack binding names httpx as
# part of the assumed pytest stack, and its contract/integration patterns drive
# the real FastAPI app over httpx.AsyncClient + ASGITransport — the endpoint
# contract tests SDD-001 §3.1 requires cannot be written without an ASGI
# client. This is a *test* dependency: it is deliberately absent from
# requirements.in, because the service makes no outbound HTTP call.
httpx>=0.26.0
